description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time for the Public Health Nursing Service in Shropshire. Successful candidates will be part of a dynamic team who are committed to improving outcomes for children and young people through service transformation and partnership working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a vacancy for a full time Specialist Community Public Health Nurse (health visitor or school nurse) to be part of Shropshire’s COMPASS team (multi agency safeguarding hub)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst this post is very part of the Public Health Nursing Service, the post holder will work as part of a dynamic multi-agency integrated team assessing notifications and referrals regarding children aged 0-19 that are received by COMPASS. The process includes searching for and collating health information from a range of NHS providers both locally and further afield. With due regard to patient confidentiality, the post holder will interpret and share the information that is necessary to safeguard and/or promote the welfare of the child/young person&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in joining our forward thinking service you will need to be flexible and adaptable with a ‘can do’ problem solving approach. In return you can expect opportunities to develop professional skills/ knowledge through the use of personal development plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is a family friendly employer, and we are happy to consider flexible working arrangements wherever possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or an informal discussion about this post, please contact Jayne Christie, Locality Lead North Shropshire Public Health Nursing Team on 07775 633357&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
